This paper is primarily focused on deep neural networks and their convergence properties, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of skip connections in network architectures, which is a popular technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) domains. The paper also compares the performance of different network architectures, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper discusses the use of autoencoders, which is a specific type of neural network used for unsupervised learning and falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
